Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String s1 = new String("hello");
String s2 = new String("hello");
System.out.println(s1 == s2);
System.out.println(s1.equals(s2));
```

Determine the value of `result` after the following code runs:

```java
int a = 7;
boolean result = a % 2 == 0;
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int score = 85;
String grade;
if (score >= 90)
    grade = "A";
else if (score >= 80)
    grade = "B";
else if (score >= 70)
    grade = "C";
else
    grade = "F";
System.out.println(grade);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String s = null;
if (s != null && s.equals("hello"))
    System.out.println("match");
else
    System.out.println("no match");
```

A student writes the following code expecting to print `same` when two strings have identical content. What is the actual output?

```java
String a = new String("java");
String b = new String("java");
if (a == b)
    System.out.println("same");
else
    System.out.println("different");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 6;
int y = 4;
if (x > y)
{
    if (x % y == 0)
        System.out.println("A");
    else
        System.out.println("B");
}
else
    System.out.println("C");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int a = 15;
int b = 4;
boolean x = a % b == 3;
boolean y = a / b >= 3;
if (x && y)
    System.out.println("both");
else if (x)
    System.out.println("first");
else if (y)
    System.out.println("second");
else
    System.out.println("neither");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int p = 8;
int q = 12;
if (p > q)
    System.out.print("A");
else
    System.out.print("B");
if (p != q)
    System.out.print("C");
if (q >= 12)
    System.out.print("D");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String s1 = new String("Java");
String s2 = new String("Java");
String s3 = s1;

if (s1 == s2)
    System.out.print("1 ");
if (s1 == s3)
    System.out.print("2 ");
if (s1.equals(s2))
    System.out.print("3");
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int num = 7;
int den = 2;
double quotient = num / den;
if (quotient == 3.5)
    System.out.print("match");
else
    System.out.print("no match");
```

