int b = 20;
int c = 10;
int count = 0;
if (a == c)    count++;
if (b > a + c) count++;
if (a != b)    count++;
System.out.println(count);
```

Consider the following code segment.

```java
int x = 12;
int y = 5;
int z = 2;

if (x / y == z)
{
    System.out.print("A");
}
else
{
    System.out.print("B");
}

if (x % y <= z)
